OL,3,C'I actually heard the blast': 40th
OL,4,Canniversary of IRA Brighton bomb
OL,6,FThe Thursday night of a Tory party
OL,7,Fconference, with all the business done
OL,8,Fand just the leader's speech to come
OL,9,Fin the morning, was traditionally a
OL,10,Ftime to let your hair down.
OL,12,FThere were several receptions with
OL,13,Flots of free booze and an opportunity
OL,14,Ffor journalists like me to mingle and
OL,15,Fnetwork with senior members of the
OL,16,Fgovernment and officials who could be
OL,17,Fuseful to know.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
