OL,3,C'I actually heard the blast': 40th
OL,4,Canniversary of IRA Brighton bomb
OL,6,FInstead she appeared in the early
OL,7,Fhours defiantly telling us the
OL,8,Fconference would go on, despite the
OL,9,Floss of five lives with many more
OL,10,Finjured.
OL,12,FIn those dramatic and confused hours
OL,13,Fwe were told that all members of the
OL,14,Fcabinet had been accounted for and
OL,15,Fwere safe. That turned out not to be
OL,16,Ftrue.
OL,18,FNorman Tebbit and his wife were later
OL,19,Ffound buried but alive. They survived
OL,20,Fbut Margaret Tebbit was paralysed from
OL,21,Fthe neck down.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
